The paper introduces a novel neural network-based feature selection architecture, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The architecture is specifically designed for image classification tasks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of backpropagation, which is a common technique in neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method on various datasets, indicating a focus on data science and machine learning (cs.DS).
